title.native: ひみつのアイプリ リング編

description:
It's a new semester! Himari and Mitsuki have become second-year students of Paradise Private Academy! Their school lives become more and more lively with the introduction of new underclassmen full of individuality and personality.

In the AiPri-Verse, new AiPri are appearing one after another! Everyone tries their hand at a brand new, never-before-seen Buzzrium Change! In the midst of all this, the mysterious Princess Ring Clover and her butler, Shimitsuu, are holding an Aipri contest. They say the winner will become an admired "Eternal Aipri." Himari and Mitsuki are all ready and full of fighting spirit! But it appears Princess Ring holds a very large secret...

As their friends increase, so does the mysteries of the ring. The Ring arc finally begins!

(Source: Offiical Website, translated)

**Education:** Yoyogi Animation Academy

[Twitter](https://twitter.com/junichifujisaku)

Junichi Fujisaku is a Japanese director, animation director, scriptwriter, game producer and novelist. He's affiliated with studio Production I.G.

[Profile (bransic)](https://bransic.net/composer_musician/izumi-mori) | [Twitter](https://x.com/mori_izumimi)

Izumi Mori is a Japanese composer, part of the musical duo *IZUMI SAKI*.

[Profile (Avex Pictures)](https://avex-pictures.co.jp/lineup/58780/) | [Twitter](https://twitter.com/fujidera_minori/)

She entered and competed in the NEXT Voice Actor Artist Audition, and was selected for the role of Auru Omega.

A Japanese girl idol group belonging to Stardust Promotion, consisting of 6 members:

- Kanami Tsujino (辻野かなみ)
- Julia An (杏ジュリア)
- Hitoka Sakai (坂井仁香)
- Haruka Koizumi (小泉遥香)
- Aki Suda (菅田愛貴)
- Hiyori Yoshikawa (吉川ひより)

**Former Members:**

- Mako Nagasaka (永坂真心)
- Sala Odaka (小高サラ)
- Bambi Fujimoto (藤本ばんび)
